reviews.text: Excellent station, good staff who actually know how to do their job, they also don't pour buckets of dirty water on homeless people unlike the incompetent staff at Sutton.
Great clean station with a ticket office and staff that can actually do their job. They also don't throw buckets of dirty water onto homeless people unlike down the line.
This is a GREAT station with HELPFUL and FRIENDLY staff (unlike Sutton) and has a small coffee shop which is run by a nice guy, very good when traveling on a cold morning.
Excellent station! This one actually has a service with a smile, and the staff actually know their train network and are helpful when you ask them questions unlike other stations on the line.
Really good station, when the station is closed there is always the railway replacement. Top up stations work, refreshment station good. Also taxis around too
